headline: How the Narrative Around Conagra Is Shifting After Weak Guidance and Analyst Reactions
summary: Conagra Brands has seen its consensus analyst price target decline slightly, moving from $20.93 to $20.58, following recent financial updates. This modest change comes after the company reported weaker-than-expected fourth-quarter results and issued outlooks that fell short of Wall Street estimates. Analysts have cited ongoing pressures such as inflation and market share losses. Stay tuned to discover how you can monitor these trends and stay informed about the evolving narrative around...
